## рҹӣ пёҸ Tech Stack

### вҡҷпёҸ Backend (`job-backend`)
- вҳ• Java 17
- рҹҢұ Spring Boot
- рҹ—ғпёҸ Spring Data JPA
- рҹҗ¬ MySQL (main DB)
- рҹ§Ә H2 (tests)
- рҹ“Ұ Maven

### рҹҺЁ Frontend (`job-frontend`)
- рҹҢҗ HTML5
- рҹҺЁ CSS3
- вҡӣпёҸ React 18 (CDN)
- рҹ§© ReactDOM + Babel Standalone
- рҹ”— Fetch API

---

## рҹ”Ң Backend API (Quick List)

- `GET /api/jobs`
- `GET /api/jobs/search?keyword=java`
- `POST /api/jobs`
- `PUT /api/jobs/{id}`
- `DELETE /api/jobs/{id}`
- `POST /api/preferences`
- `GET /api/recommendations/{preferenceId}`

---

## рҹҡҖ How to Run the Project

## 1пёҸвғЈ Run Backend

From `job-backend` folder:

```bash
./mvnw spring-boot:run
```

Backend runs on:
- `http://localhost:8080`

Set DB variables in PowerShell before running:

```powershell
$env:DB_URL="jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/job_portal"
$env:DB_USERNAME="root"
$env:DB_PASSWORD="your_mysql_password"
```

---

## 2пёҸвғЈ Run Frontend

Open files from `job-frontend`:

- рҹҸ  `index.html`
- рҹ’ј `jobs.html`
- рҹҺҜ `tailored.html`

You can open directly in browser, or use a local server (recommended) for smoother development.

